From: Sebastian Andrzej Siewior <bigeasy@linutronix.de>
Date: Tue, 9 Feb 2016 18:18:01 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 140/352] kernel: migrate_disable() do fastpath in atomic &
 irqs-off

With interrupts off it makes no sense to do the long path since we can't
leave the CPU anyway. Also we might end up in a recursion with lockdep.

Signed-off-by: Sebastian Andrzej Siewior <bigeasy@linutronix.de>
---
 kernel/sched/core.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/kernel/sched/core.c b/kernel/sched/core.c
index c84ad5d..606b004 100644
--- a/kernel/sched/core.c
+++ b/kernel/sched/core.c
@@ -3416,7 +3416,7 @@ void migrate_disable(void)
 {
 	struct task_struct *p = current;
 
-	if (in_atomic()) {
+	if (in_atomic() || irqs_disabled()) {
 #ifdef CONFIG_SCHED_DEBUG
 		p->migrate_disable_atomic++;
 #endif
@@ -3443,7 +3443,7 @@ void migrate_enable(void)
 {
 	struct task_struct *p = current;
 
-	if (in_atomic()) {
+	if (in_atomic() || irqs_disabled()) {
 #ifdef CONFIG_SCHED_DEBUG
 		p->migrate_disable_atomic--;
 #endif
-- 
